festival.introText:
WORRIED ABOUT HENRY

DREAMLAND | MARGATE

Saturday 24th June 2023 | 3pm - 11pm

An all-day bass-orientated event at Margate’s iconic seafront destination the scenic stage. 16+ (Under 18's must be accompanied by an adult)An all-day Drum & Bass event at Margate’s iconic seafront destination

 

Taking over Dreamland, Margate’s all-you-can-treat seaside entertainment sensation, thousands of Drum & Bass fans from far and wide will find a who’s who of top tier DJs performing throughout the day, with a dozen artists putting the venue through its paces from 15:00 – 23:00.

Worried About Henry made a huge impact on Dreamland’s open air stage last year, bringing a wicked day of Drum and Bass, sun and excellent vibes from start to finish. This year they are set to send ripples across the ocean as they return with heavy-weight duo Chase & Status for a DJ set, returning legend, Shy FX, and 2022’s hottest new artist, Hedex; plus a wealth of top Drum & Bass artists, announcing soon in the phase 2 announcement..

With a brand new studio album in 2022, What Came Before, Chase & Status reached new levels of creative decadence. Taking their iconic sound to far corners, they toured the world with style, helping the genre to once again reach new heights. They are set to bring nothing short of excellence to Dreamland this June with their renowned DJ set. Shy FX, with a career spanning almost 3 decades, also joins the bill to bring his iconic sound of underground sonics blended with  illustrious vocals to Dreamland’s vibrant stage; as well as new boy on the block, Hedex, with his revitalised style of jump-up productions, fast paced DJ sets and epic collection of bass-bangers sure to set the tone for summer. Many more amazing names to be announced soon.

This is a must have event in any Drum & Bass fan’s calendar, and an unmissable chance to experience the best the scene has to offer in one of the UK’s most unique coastal locations.
